    <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label"><i class="fas fa-search-location"></i> Nearby Chargers</span>
            <h1>How to Find EV Charging Stations Near You</h1>
            <p>Use maps, app filters, and local charger data to quickly locate the nearest EV charging station.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="container container--narrow">
            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Ask the right question</h2>
                <p>When you search for "EV charging station near me," Google and dedicated EV apps should return nearby options with distance, connector type, and availability. Combining multiple tools gives you the best chance of finding a charger that fits your trip.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Best tools to use</h2>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-map"></i></span><div><strong>ChargeKR:</strong> Shows shared and public chargers with ratings, price, and booking capability.</div></div>
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-globe"></i></span><div><strong>Google Maps:</strong> Great for public charging station locations and driving directions.</div></div>
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-car-side"></i></span><div><strong>In-car navigation:</strong> Use your EV’s built-in charger finder for on-route results.</div></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Key search filters</h2>
                <p>Look for filters that let you choose:</p>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i></span><div><strong>Charger speed:</strong> slow, fast, or DC fast options.</div></div>
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-plug"></i></span><div><strong>Connector type:</strong> CCS, CHAdeMO, Type 2, or J1772 compatibility.</div></div>
                    <div class="feature-list-item"><span class="check"><i class="fas fa-star"></i></span><div><strong>Ratings:</strong> recent reviews from people who used the charger.</div></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>How to choose the best option</h2>
                <p>Prefer chargers with recent availability data, strong ratings, and a connector type that matches your EV. If you need a quick charge, pick a DC fast charger. If you’re parking for a few hours, a slower public or shared charger can be more affordable.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top:24px;">
